I've been playing around with the method and have noticed this: 

``` csharp
if (t.IsGenericType && t.GetGenericTypeDefinition() == typeof(Dictionary<,>))
{
    var result = "";
    var dict = (System.Collections.IDictionary)v;
    foreach (var kvp in dict)
    {
        var key = ((System.Collections.DictionaryEntry)kvp).Key;
        var value = ((System.Collections.DictionaryEntry)kvp).Value;

        var formattedKey = FormatValue(key);
        var formattedValue = FormatValue(value);

        result += "{0}: {1}{2}".F(formattedKey, formattedValue, Environment.NewLine);
    }

    return result;
}
```

Which results in a dictionary containing {[ra, russia], [ts, gdi], [d2k, Random]} to become:

``` yaml
Game:
    LastFaction: ra: russia
ts: gdi
d2k: Random
```

is this correct? Am I right in thinking that this method formats values for writing to YAML files? If so, then wouldn't it be something along the lines of:

``` csharp
    result += Environment.NewLine;
    foreach (var kvp in dict)
            {
                var key = ((System.Collections.DictionaryEntry)kvp).Key;
                var value = ((System.Collections.DictionaryEntry)kvp).Value;

                var formattedKey = FormatValue(key);
                var formattedValue = FormatValue(value);

      result += "{0}{1}: {2}{3}".F("\t\t", formattedKey, formattedValue, Environment.NewLine);
    }
```

, which gives a result which the YAML reader reads as a Dictionary correctly:

``` yaml
Game:
    LastFaction:
        ra: russia
        ts: gdi
        d2k: Random
```

